i found the manga looking ones on a random wallpaper site having dumb names like: j7hrgnmj67i8j5.etc i found them impressive looking (for anime) so i saved them.
after i saved them in my wallpaper map i found them clustered around a image that did had something to do with new york. 
me, being a lazy turd, i simply selected them all and called them new york so i could easily find them again when i started imagesearching/saucenao them for the real artist and names. when i renamed them to their correct names and added the artist who made them they scattered around my wallpaper map. so i added the new york prefix to anything remotely urban. (i have the forest prefix for tree wallpapers, desert for desert/badlands/arid etc.

also, the first post with the abstract ones is superior. even more impressive that almost all of them pre date 2006.
